SLIDE 14 — ISSUE IDENTIFIED AFTER DEPLOYMENT
“After deployment in PROD, an issue was identified related to Snowflake’s supported maximum date values.
Snowflake supports date values such as 9999-12-31 and 1900-01-01.
However, Pandas could not properly process these edge-case date values during conversion.
This caused data type mismatch issues during the update process.
As a result, updates failed for records containing those dates.”
SLIDE 15 — SOLUTION FOR DATE HANDLING
“To resolve this issue, custom date normalization logic was implemented.
Explicit handling was added for Snowflake edge-case dates such as 9999-12-31 and 1900-01-01.
Instead of allowing Pandas to process those values normally, the application now safely handles them before conversion occurs.
This prevented conversion failures and maintained compatibility between Streamlit, Pandas, and Snowflake date handling.
Overall, the solution improved application stability and reliability.”
